      • generateReplacementMap

        public static Map<byte[],byte[]> generateReplacementMap(Map<Path,Path> pathMap)
        Prepares a replacement map for prefixes. For example, if had two entries: 1. "/path/to/repo" -> "", 2. "/path/to/repo/cell" -> "cell"

        The resulting map would contain: 1. "/path/to/repo/" -> "./" 2. "/path/to/repo/cell/" -> "cell/"

        The above means we can do very simple (and fast!) search & replace.

      • tryRewritingMatchingPath

        public static Optional<ByteBuffer> tryRewritingMatchingPath(byte[] stringBytes,
                                                            int stringOffset,
                                                            Map<byte[],byte[]> replacementMap)
        Checks whether a string matches a prefix and returns a rewritten copy if that's the case. For example, given a string "/Users/fb/repo/cell" and a replacement map containing "/Users/fb/repo/" -> "./", it will return a ByteBuffer wrapping "./cell".

        NB: This is a perf sensitive method.
